stop all runninng containers
docker stop $(docker ps -q) -- lists all the runninf conatiners

docker system prune -a
this will remove all stopped containers
all networks not used by atleast one container
all build cache

# run docker image by pulling it directly from dockerHub
 docker run -d -p 8081:8080 rondocker2191/credit-card 
 
#push to docker hub
docker push rondocker2191/credit-card  -- this will go ahead and create a repository in your docker hub account with credit-card name

# build a docker image
docker build -t rondcoker2191/credit-card .
then push it to odkcer hub
docker push rondocker2191/credit-card


Why Docker Kubernetes
Docker containerising apps .. standard/ same packaging for all types of applications
just have the docker machine and can run all the apps

To start a container  for example to start in local
docker start postgres-container

